headline: Why Carrier Global (CARR) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of heating, ventilation, air conditioning, and refrigeration company Carrier Global (NYSE:CARR) jumped 3.3% in the afternoon session after its venture arm, Carrier Ventures, made a strategic investment in Net Feasa, a company specializing in wireless IoT connectivity for the shipping industry.
